	(492, 'Digital Temperature sensor, 0.1 °C accuracy, TO18', '<p>The SMT172-TO18 is an ultra-low power, fully calibrated, high accuracy digital sensor. Using the most recent advances in silicon temperature sensing technology, the SMT172 has applied sophisticated IC design techniques and high-precision calibration methods, to achieve an overall accuracy of 0.1ºC in the range of -20ºC to 100ºC (-4ºF to 212ºF) and an accuracy of 0.4ºC from -45ºC to -20ºC and 100ºC to 135ºC.  Measuring the SMT172 sensor requires only one digital pin. <br><br>* Overall accuracy 0.1ºC in the temperature range of -20ºC to 80ºC. (TO18)<br>* Overall accuracy 0.25ºC in the temperature range of -10ºC to 100ºC.<br>* Accuracy of 0.4ºC from -45ºC to -20ºC and from 100ºC to 135ºC<br>* Noise less then 0.0001ºC<br>* Full temperature range from -45ºC to -135ºC (-49ºF to 275ºF)<br>* PWM output is easy to read by the a microprocessor.<br>* PWM signal is proportional to the temperature.<br>* Supply voltage 3V, 3.3V, 5V (Voltage range from +2.7V to +5.5V).<br>* 3 pin sensor, requires only one digital pin. ( Vcc, Gnd, PWM output ).</p>', 114),
	(493, 'Digital Temperature sensor, 0.25 °C accuracy, TO92', '<p>The SMT172-TO92 is an ultra-low power, fully calibrated, high accuracy digital sensor. Using the most recent advances in silicon temperature sensing technology, the SMT172 has applied sophisticated IC design techniques and high-precision calibration methods, to achieve an overall accuracy of 0.1ºC in the range of -20ºC to 100ºC (-4ºF to 212ºF) and an accuracy of 0.4ºC from -45ºC to -20ºC and 100ºC to 135ºC.  Measuring the SMT172 sensor requires only one digital pin. <br><br>* Overall accuracy 0.25ºC in the temperature range of -20ºC to 80ºC. (TO92)<br>* Use SMT172-TO18 for best 0.1ºC accuracy <br>* Accuracy of 0.8ºC from -45ºC to -20ºC and from 100ºC to 135ºC<br>* Noise less then 0.0001ºC<br>* Full temperature range from -45ºC to -135ºC (-49ºF to 275ºF)<br>* PWM output is easy to read by the a microprocessor.<br>* PWM signal is proportional to the temperature.<br>* Supply voltage 3V, 3.3V, 5V (Voltage range from +2.7V to +5.5V).<br>* 3 pin sensor, requires only one digital pin. ( Vcc, Gnd, PWM output ).</p>', 114),
	(494, 'Digital Temperature sensor, 0.25 °C accuracy, TO220', '<p>The SMT172-TO220 is an ultra-low power, fully calibrated, high accuracy digital sensor. Using the most recent advances in silicon temperature sensing technology, the SMT172 has applied sophisticated IC design techniques and high-precision calibration methods, to achieve an overall accuracy of 0.1ºC in the range of -20ºC to 100ºC (-4ºF to 212ºF) and an accuracy of 0.4ºC from -45ºC to -20ºC and 100ºC to 135ºC.  Measuring the SMT172 sensor requires only one digital pin.<br><br>* Overall accuracy 0.25ºC in the temperature range of -20ºC to 80ºC. (TO92)<br>* Use SMT172-TO18 for best 0.1ºC accuracy <br>* Accuracy of 0.8ºC from -45ºC to -20ºC and from 100ºC to 135ºC<br>* Noise less then 0.0001ºC<br>* Full temperature range from -45ºC to -135ºC (-49ºF to 275ºF)<br>* PWM output is easy to read by the a microprocessor.<br>* PWM signal is proportional to the temperature.<br>* Supply voltage 3V, 3.3V, 5V (Voltage range from +2.7V to +5.5V).<br>* 3 pin sensor, requires only one digital pin. ( Vcc, Gnd, PWM output ).</p>', 114),
	(495, 'Digital Temperature sensor, 0.25 °C accuracy, SOT223', '<p>The SMT172-TO223 is an ultra-low power, fully calibrated, high accuracy digital sensor. Using the most recent advances in silicon temperature sensing technology, the SMT172 has applied sophisticated IC design techniques and high-precision calibration methods, to achieve an overall accuracy of 0.1ºC in the range of -20ºC to 100ºC (-4ºF to 212ºF) and an accuracy of 0.4ºC from -45ºC to -20ºC and 100ºC to 135ºC.  Measuring the SMT172 sensor requires only one digital pin.<br><br>* Overall accuracy 0.25ºC in the temperature range of -20ºC to 80ºC. (TO92)<br>* Use SMT172-TO18 for best 0.1ºC accuracy <br>* Accuracy of 0.8ºC from -45ºC to -20ºC and from 100ºC to 135ºC<br>* Noise less then 0.0001ºC<br>* Full temperature range from -45ºC to -135ºC (-49ºF to 275ºF)<br>* PWM output is easy to read by the a microprocessor.<br>* PWM signal is proportional to the temperature.<br>* Supply voltage 3V, 3.3V, 5V (Voltage range from +2.7V to +5.5V).<br>* 3 pin sensor, requires only one digital pin. ( Vcc, Gnd, PWM output ).</p>', 114),
	(496, 'Digital Temperature sensor, 0.25 °C accuracy, HEC', '<p>The SMT172-HEC is an ultra-low power, fully calibrated, high accuracy digital sensor. Using the most recent advances in silicon temperature sensing technology, the SMT172 has applied sophisticated IC design techniques and high-precision calibration methods, to achieve an overall accuracy of 0.1ºC in the range of -20ºC to 100ºC (-4ºF to 212ºF) and an accuracy of 0.4ºC from -45ºC to -20ºC and 100ºC to 135ºC. Measuring the SMT172 sensor requires only one digital pin.<br /><br />* Overall accuracy 0.25ºC in the temperature range of -20ºC to 80ºC. (TO92)<br />* Use SMT172-TO18 for best 0.1ºC accuracy <br />* Accuracy of 0.8ºC from -45ºC to -20ºC and from 100ºC to 135ºC<br />* Noise less then 0.0001ºC<br />* Full temperature range from -45ºC to -135ºC (-49ºF to 275ºF)<br />* PWM output is easy to read by the a microprocessor.<br />* PWM signal is proportional to the temperature.<br />* Supply voltage 3V, 3.3V, 5V (Voltage range from +2.7V to +5.5V).<br />* 3 pin sensor, requires only one digital pin. ( Vcc, Gnd, PWM output ).</p>\r\n', 114),
	(497, 'Digital Temperature sensor, 0.25 °C accuracy, SOIC', '<p>The SMT172-SOIC is an ultra-low power, fully calibrated, high accuracy digital sensor. Using the most recent advances in silicon temperature sensing technology, the SMT172 has applied sophisticated IC design techniques and high-precision calibration methods, to achieve an overall accuracy of 0.1ºC in the range of -20ºC to 100ºC (-4ºF to 212ºF) and an accuracy of 0.4ºC from -45ºC to -20ºC and 100ºC to 135ºC.  Measuring the SMT172 sensor requires only one digital pin.<br><br>* Overall accuracy 0.25ºC in the temperature range of -20ºC to 80ºC. (TO92)<br>* Use SMT172-TO18 for best 0.1ºC accuracy <br>* Accuracy of 0.8ºC from -45ºC to -20ºC and from 100ºC to 135ºC<br>* Noise less then 0.0001ºC<br>* Full temperature range from -45ºC to -135ºC (-49ºF to 275ºF)<br>* PWM output is easy to read by the a microprocessor.<br>* PWM signal is proportional to the temperature.<br>* Supply voltage 3V, 3.3V, 5V (Voltage range from +2.7V to +5.5V).<br>* 3 pin sensor, requires only one digital pin. ( Vcc, Gnd, PWM output ).</p>', 114),
	(498, 'Digital Temperature probe sensor, 0.1 °C accuracy', '<p>A stainless steel probe with the most accurate the temperature sensor SMT172-TO18 built-in. The stainless steel tube of the probe has diameter of 7.0mm x 40mm long. Supplied with a 5 mtr shielded cable. (Connection Brown = Vcc, Green = GND, White = PWM output). <br><br>* Overall accuracy 0.1ºC in the temperature range of -20ºC to 80ºC. (TO18)<br>* Overall accuracy 0.25ºC in the temperature range of -10ºC to 100ºC.<br>* Accuracy of 0.4ºC from -45ºC to -20ºC and from 100ºC to 135ºC<br>* Noise less then 0.0001ºC<br>* Full temperature range from -45ºC to -135ºC (-49ºF to 275ºF)<br>* PWM output is easy to read by the a microprocessor.<br>* PWM signal is proportional to the temperature.<br>* Supply voltage 3V, 3.3V, 5V (Voltage range from +2.7V to +5.5V).<br>* 3 pin sensor, requires only one digital pin. ( Vcc, Gnd, PWM output ).</p>', 114),
	(499, 'Digital Temperature probe, 0.25 °C accuracy, fine tip', '<p>A pointed stainless steel probe with the SMT172-HEC temperature sensor built-in.  5.0mm diameter x 150mm long stainless steel probe with a 5 mtr shielded cable. (Connection Brown = Vcc, Green = GND, White = PWM output). <br><br>Time constant in non stired fluid is 5sec.<br>* Overall accuracy 0.25ºC in the temperature range of -20ºC to 80ºC. (TO18)<br>* Accuracy of 0.8ºC from -45ºC to -20ºC and from 100ºC to 135ºC<br>* Noise less then 0.0001ºC<br>* Full temperature range from -45ºC to -135ºC (-49ºF to 275ºF)<br>* PWM output is easy to read by the a microprocessor.<br>* PWM signal is proportional to the temperature.<br>* Supply voltage 3V, 3.3V, 5V (Voltage range from +2.7V to +5.5V).<br>* 3 pin sensor, requires only one digital pin. ( Vcc, Gnd, PWM output ).</p>', 114),
	(500, 'USB Development board measures upto 4 temperature sensors', '<p> The SMTAS04USB evaluation board can measure upto 4 x SMT172 temperature sensors with an accuracy of 0.1ºC in the temperature range of -10ºC to 100ºC with a resolution of 0.0015 C.  Accuracy of 0.4ºC from -45ºC to -20ºC and from 100ºC to 135ºC. The board and sensors can be powered from the USB port or from an external DC power supply. The board uses an ARM Cortex-M3 STM32F103 to read the temperature sensors and output the measured values of the sensors PWM signal in HEX on the USB interface. </p>', 114),
	(501, 'USB Development board measures upto 4  temperature sensors', '<p>The SMTAS08USB evaluation board can measure upto 8 x SMT172 temperature sensors with an accuracy of 0.1ºC in the temperature range of -10ºC to 100ºC with a resolution of 0.0015 C.  Accuracy of 0.4ºC from -45ºC to -20ºC and from 100ºC to 135ºC. The board and sensors can be powered from the USB port or from an external DC power supply. The board uses an ARM Cortex-M3 STM32F103 to read the temperature sensors and output the measured values of the sensors PWM signal in HEX on the USB interface. </p>', 114),
	(502, 'SMT172 to I2C Converter board', '<p>This little interface board allows the SMT172 sensor to connect to an I2C bus. The SMT172TOI2C can convert the SMT172 output to be compatible with the obsolete SMT160-30 sensor. This board can be used for repair of equipment that used the obsolete SMT160-30 sensor.</p>', 114),
	(503, 'Smartec UTI Sensor to Digital Transducer, DIL', '<p>The Smartec Universal Transducer Interface (UTI) is a complete analog front end for low frequency measurement applications, based on a period-modulated oscillator. Sensing elements can be directly connected to the UTI without the need for extra electronics.  Only a single reference component, of the same kind as the sensor is required. The UTI outputs a microcontroller compatible period-modulated signal. The transducer can measure very accurately capacitance, platinum resistors, thermistors and resistive bridges. To accelerate sensor design with the SMT UTI an evaluation board SMT TOOLKIT is available.<br><br>* Full sensor solution on a chip<br>* Sensing elements can be directly connected to the UTI without the need for extra electronics.<br>* Single supply voltage 2.9V to 5.5V, 2.5mA supply<br>* Continues auto calibration of offset and gain.<br>* Typical measurement time 10mS or 100mS<br>* Capacitive sensors modes: 0 to2pF,  0 to 12pF and &lt;300pF<br>* Platinum resistors Pt100, Pt1000<br>* Resistive bridges 250 Ohm to 10kOhm with maximum imbalance ±4% or ±0.25%<br>* 2,3 or 4 wire measurement modes for resistive measurements<br>* AC excitation voltage for all sensor elements<br>* Suppression for interference of 50Hz and 60Hz<br>* Applications: Capacittive level sensing and distance sensing, position and angle sensing, Wheatstone bridge setup for pressure, force, platinum, NTC...</p>', 118),
	(504, 'Smartec UTI Sensor to Digital Transducer,  SOIC', '<p>The Smartec Universal Transducer Interface (UTI) is a complete analog front end for low frequency measurement applications, based on a period-modulated oscillator. Sensing elements can be directly connected to the UTI without the need for extra electronics.  Only a single reference component, of the same kind as the sensor is required. The UTI outputs a microcontroller compatible period-modulated signal. The transducer can measure very accurately capacitance, platinum resistors, thermistors and resistive bridges. To accelerate sensor design with the SMT UTI an evaluation board SMT TOOLKIT is available.<br><br>* Full sensor solution on a chip<br>* Sensing elements can be directly connected to the UTI without the need for extra electronics.<br>* Single supply voltage 2.9V to 5.5V, 2.5mA supply<br>* Continues auto calibration of offset and gain.<br>* Typical measurement time 10mS or 100mS<br>* Capacitive sensors modes: 0 to2pF,  0 to 12pF and &lt;300pF<br>* Platinum resistors Pt100, Pt1000<br>* Resistive bridges 250 Ohm to 10kOhm with maximum imbalance ±4% or ±0.25%<br>* 2,3 or 4 wire measurement modes for resistive measurements<br>* AC excitation voltage for all sensor elements<br>* Suppression for interference of 50Hz and 60Hz<br>* Applications: Capacittive level sensing and distance sensing, position and angle sensing, Wheatstone bridge setup for pressure, force, platinum, NTC...</p>', 118),
	(505, 'Smartec UTI Sensor to Digital Evaluation board, USB', '<p>The Smartec SMT TOOLKIT is an evaluation board to speedup sensor design with the Universal Transducer Interface (UTI). The UTI is a complete analog front end for low frequency measurement applications, based on a period-modulated oscillator. Sensing elements can be directly connected to the UTI without the need for extra electronics.  Only a single reference component, of the same kind as the sensor is required. The UTI outputs a microcontroller compatible period-modulated signal. The transducer can measure very accurately capacitance, platinum resistors, thermistors and resistive bridges. The SMT TOOLKIT connects via USB to PC software. The measured results from the UTI are displayed on the PC or laptop. Mode selection can be changed from the software.<br><br>* Full sensor solution on a chip<br>* Sensing elements can be directly connected to the UTI without the need for extra electronics<br>* Single supply voltage 2.9V to 5.5V, 2.5mA supply. Power taken from the USB port<br>* Continues auto calibration of offset and gain<br>* Typical measurement time 10mS or 100mS<br>* Capacitive sensors modes: 0 to2pF,  0 to 12pF and &lt;300pF<br>* Platinum resistors Pt100, Pt1000<br>* Resistive bridges 250 Ohm to 10kOhm with maximum imbalance ±4% or ±0.25%<br>* 2,3 or 4 wire measurement modes for resistive measurements<br>* AC excitation voltage for all sensor elements<br>* Suppression for interference of 50Hz and 60Hz<br>* Applications: Capacittive level sensing and distance sensing, position and angle sensing, Wheatstone bridge setup for pressure, force, platinum, NTC...</p>', 118),
	(506, 'Smartec UTI Sensor to Digital Evaluation board, RS232', '<p>The Smartec SMT TOOLKIT is an evaluation board to speedup sensor design with the Universal Transducer Interface (UTI). The UTI is a complete analog front end for low frequency measurement applications, based on a period-modulated oscillator. Sensing elements can be directly connected to the UTI without the need for extra electronics.  Only a single reference component, of the same kind as the sensor is required. The UTI outputs a microcontroller compatible period-modulated signal. The transducer can measure very accurately capacitance, platinum resistors, thermistors and resistive bridges. The SMT TOOLKIT connects via an RS232 port  to PC software. The measured results from the UTI are displayed on the PC or laptop. Mode selection can be changed from the software.<br><br>* Full sensor solution on a chip<br>* Sensing elements can be directly connected to the UTI without the need for extra electronics<br>* Single supply voltage 2.9V to 5.5V, 2.5mA supply (UTI) and 9-12V for SMT TOOLKIT<br>* Continues auto calibration of offset and gain<br>* Typical measurement time 10mS or 100mS<br>* Capacitive sensors modes: 0 to2pF,  0 to 12pF and &lt;300pF<br>* Platinum resistors Pt100, Pt1000<br>* Resistive bridges 250 Ohm to 10kOhm with maximum imbalance ±4% or ±0.25%<br>* 2,3 or 4 wire measurement modes for resistive measurements<br>* AC excitation voltage for all sensor elements<br>* Suppression for interference of 50Hz and 60Hz<br>* Applications: Capacittive level sensing and distance sensing, position and angle sensing, Wheatstone bridge setup for pressure, force, platinum, NTC...</p>', 118),
	(507, 'Smartec multiplexer for capacitor sensors', '<p>The Smartec SMT MUX-DIL is a designed to select up to 9 capacitors to on input. Mostly used in combination with the SMT UTI when UTI is setup for capacitance sensing CMUX mode. <br><br>* ESD protected input and outputs<br>* Large capacitive driving capability<br>* Single supply voltage 2.7V to 6.0V<br>* Low output impediance<br>* Other partnumbers: SMT MUX-DIL = MUX03<br>* Applications: capacitive sensors, capacitive angle and level sensing </p>', 118),
	(508, 'Smartec multiplexer for capacitor sensors', '<p>The Smartec SMT MUX-SOIC is a designed to select up to 9 capacitors to on input. Mostly used in combination with the SMT UTI when UTI is setup for capacitance sensing CMUX mode. <br><br>* ESD protected input and outputs<br>* Large capacitive driving capability<br>* Single supply voltage 2.7V to 6.0V<br>* Low output impediance<br>* Other partnumbers: SMT MUX-SOIC = MUXEN01<br>* Applications: capacitive sensors, capacitive angle and level sensing </p>', 118),
	(509, 'USTI Sensor to Digital Transducer serial, SPI and I2C Interface', '<p>The Universal Sensors and Transducers Interface ( USTI ) is a fully digital CMOS integrated circuit for use with any sensor or transducer with a frequency, period, duty-cycle, interval, PWM , phase shift or pulse number output.  The USTI is perfectly suited to any applications where frequency-time parameters or sensors output signals need to be measured with highest resolution and programmable accuracy. Non-redundant conversion time. The design is based on novel advanced methods for frequency, period, duty-cycle and phase-shift  measurements. Available as PDIP, TQFP,MLF and DIE packages.<br><br>The USTI covers a wide range of frequencies and accuracies for modern frequency-time domain sensors. In addition, the USTI provides interfacing for resistive (including platinum, cuprum resistors and thermistors), capacitive sensing elements and resistive bridges. The device represents a high-resolution conversion and is designed to support all range of frequency-time domain and digital sensor applications. The USTI  offers high performance with flexibility and requires minimum external components.<br><br>* 2 channels sensor solution on a chip<br>* Single supply voltage 4.5V to 5.5V<br>* Programmable accuracy for frequency conversion 0.0005% to 1%<br>* Scalable resolution<br>* Capacitive measurement from 50pF to 100µF<br>* Platinum and Cuprum (Cu) resistors Pt100, Pt1000 <br>* Resistive bridges 10 Ohm to 10MΩ<br>* Applications: Physical, chemical and biosensors, smart sensors, virtual instruments, capacitive sensing, frequency measurement<br><br>By using this IC it is possible to build a wide variety of digital, smart sensors and intelligent sensor systems. The device represents a high-resolution conversion and designed to support all range of frequency-time domain and digital sensor applications. It offers high performances with flexibility and requires minimum possible number of external components. The USTI can be easy included into digital environment, controlled by an external microcontroller (slave mode) or work independently as a separate measuring unit without an external control (master mode). The function selection can be configured in both software and hardware.</p>', 118),
