	(586, 'Demoboard for uniTFTs : CLIMA', '<p>Demo application for EA uniTFTs028 display with application PCB for CO2 measurement, temperature measurement and humidity measurement via I²C.</p>\r\n<p>The Si7020-A20 sensor is used for the temperature and humidity measurement and CSS811B-JOPD500 for the CO2 sensor.</p>\r\n<p>This applications shows communication of the sensors and Real-Time-Clock (RTC) via  I²C. RTC is battery buffered.  Demoboard has a reset switch and test points for GND and VDD.</p>\r\n<p>The display included is the SMART EA uniTFTs028-ATC 2.8" TFT with PCAP touch-screen and powerful graphics functions, memory and touch panel support. The uniTFT(s) displays can be programmed as stand-alone HMI controller with inputs and outputs. Display interface is USB (5V), serial, I²C and SPI (3.3V). A level converter is required for RS-232 (+/-12V). For an example of an application with a RS-232, RS-485 level converter check the EA DEMOPACK-CONNI.</p>\r\n<p>Move objects on the display, change measured values while they are displayed, automatically enlarge important parameters, show and hide controls.</p>\r\n<p>The EA uniTFTs028-ATC is programmed with the new drag and drop uniTFTDesigner software for Windows™.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n', 108);
